@*
    DemoBanner — issue #377.

    Site-wide strip announcing that this is the throwaway public demo, showing the
    published operator credentials and counting down to the next hourly wipe.

    Renders NOTHING unless DemoModeInfo.IsEnabled, i.e. unless PUBLIC_DEMO=true, which
    only docker-compose.demo.yml sets. DemoBannerTests asserts that on a normal
    instance the component produces no markup and leaks no credential text.

    Placement: mounted ABOVE the topbar in MainLayout and PublicLayout, deliberately
    outside the telemetry surface. The banner is amber (--status-degraded) because that
    is the universal "not production" signal, but a status page also uses amber to mean
    "a service is degraded" — keeping it out of the panel region is what stops the two
    readings from colliding. Service LEDs, uptime strips and status tags keep their own
    semantic tokens; demo mode never recolours them.

    The countdown ticks client-side from DemoMode.NextResetUtc, the same helper the
    reset timer's schedule is documented against (OnCalendar=hourly). No API call and no
    shared state: both sides read the wall clock.
*@
@using System.Threading
@using SuperStatus.ServiceDefaults
@implements IDisposable
@inject DemoModeInfo Demo

@if (Demo.IsEnabled)
{
    <div class="demo-banner" role="status">
        <span class="glyph">
            <span class="led" aria-hidden="true"></span>Public demo
        </span>
        <span class="body">
            Sign in with <code>@DemoEmail</code> / <code>@DemoPassword</code>.
            All data is <strong>wiped hourly</strong> and the latest release redeployed.
        </span>
        <span class="reset">
            <span class="k">Reset in</span>
            <span class="v">@_countdown</span>
        </span>
    </div>
}

@code {
    // Duplicated as literals rather than referenced from SuperStatus.Data: Web has no
    // reference to that project, and these are published constants, not secrets.
    private const string DemoEmail = "admin@superstatus.io";
    private const string DemoPassword = "admin";

    private string _countdown = "--:--";
    private Timer? _timer;

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        if (!Demo.IsEnabled)
        {
            return;
        }

        Refresh();
        var period = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(1);
        _timer = new Timer(_ =>
        {
            Refresh();
            InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged);
        }, null, period, period);
    }

    private void Refresh()
    {
        var remaining = DemoMode.TimeUntilReset(DateTime.UtcNow);

        // At T-0 the reset is in flight: containers are being recreated and the site is
        // about to 502 for a minute or two. Saying "now" is honest; counting into
        // negatives, or freezing at 00:00, is not.
        _countdown = remaining <= TimeSpan.Zero
            ? "now"
            : $"{(int)remaining.TotalMinutes:D2}:{remaining.Seconds:D2}";
    }

    public void Dispose()
    {
        _timer?.Dispose();
        _timer = null;
    }
}
